# Trunk workflow (main only)

This repository uses a **single branch (`main`)** and a **single working checkout**. No parallel git state.

Verified work belongs on **`main`** and must be **pushed** so CI and Vercel can run.

- Follow **AGENTS.md**: push directly to `main`, do not open PRs for routine work, do not leave finished changes stranded on a branch.
- **Do not use `git worktree add`** (or any second checkout path) for RyanRealty work — no extra working trees; they leave work “hanging” where the other tool cannot see it.
- **Do not create local or remote feature branches** for routine work. If a branch was created by mistake, merge/rebase into `main`, push, then delete the branch locally and on `origin`.
- If you ever used a local branch for safety, **merge or rebase into `main` and push** immediately; do not treat the branch as the source of truth.

Do **not** use a separate “release branch” model. See also `.cursor/rules/production-parity.mdc` and `.cursor/rules/deploy-verify-before-done.mdc`.
